-- Pearson May Place Bid for Brazilian Education Company Anglo, FT Reports
-- Lukanyo Mnyanda
-- 2010-07-03T10:49:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-03/pearson-may-place-bid-for-brazilian-education-company-anglo-ft-reports.html

          
          
             Pearson Plc  may bid for a Brazilian
education company Credit Suisse Group AG valued at as much as
600 million reais ($338.6 million), the Financial Times
reported, citing people familiar with the matter.  
 The company, known as Anglo, said it was not for sale, the
FT reported.  
 Grupo Abril, a Brazilian media company and Santillana, a
Spanish publisher, also may be interested in buying the company,
according to the newspaper. Pearson is publisher of the
Financial Times.  
